'''''You Scare Me to Death''''' is a posthumous album credited to [[Marc Bolan]] of [[T. Rex (band)|T. Rex]]. Released in 1981 by record label [[Cherry Red Records|Cherry Red]], it is first LP of material released after his death in 1977.

== Content ==

The album consists of outtakes and demos recorded by Bolan in 1966. Some of the songs would later be recorded by Bolan's band, [[T. Rex (band)|Tyrannosaurus Rex]]. Most of these tracks have also been released in their original form on the album, ''The Beginning of Doves'' (1974). In 1981, backing instrumentals were recorded and added to Bolan's original recordings.

== Release ==

''You Scare Me to Death'' was released in 1981 by record label [[Cherry Red Records|Cherry Red]]. It album reached No. 88 on the [[UK Albums Chart]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.officialcharts.com/artist/_/t.%20rex/ |title=T. Rex <nowiki>| Artist |</nowiki> Official Charts |website=[[Official Charts Company|Official Charts]] |accessdate=7 February 2015}}</ref> The title track was originally called "Horrible Breath" and was written as a proposed television jingle for Amplex tablets.{{citation needed|date=February 2015}}

